HackingDrone::CheckAxis

This steps from one point to another, looking for the point at which we intersect any room.

This is used by PickDestination to find where we should land.


HackingDrone::Destination

This picks the path the drone takes to attack a given room, notably including
the location the drone will land at.

This is done as follows:

* Pick a side (left/right/top/bottom) to attack from.
* Go through each room x/y (depending on side) coordinate, finding the position
  the drone would land if it flew to that room.
* If this position would hit the room directly, stop the loop here and select it.
* Measure the distance between the landing position and the centre of the target room.
* Pick the closest destination, or the first one if there's a tie.

The start position will be -400 or 800 in one of the x or y axes (the one that
isn't used to varied to select the landing direction).


-- Room spark rendering

When a system is hacked, the stun_spark_big animation is played on it's floor.

If a room is one cell wide or high, a 35-pixel window in the sparks image is randomly
selected and this is played back (rotated 90° if needed).

Otherwise, the full animation is played with no masking, and a random
multiple-of-90-deg rotation.

These random values are re-picked each time the animation loops.
